# Data↔text FUSION overlay (document-ontology layer §A.6) — DEMO FIXTURE.
#
# This wires a measured property curve to the document layer: the FIGURE it was
# digitized from and the SENTENCE that states how it was measured. It is the
# headline of the doc layer — a cross-modal join RAG cannot do deterministically
# ("this number, that figure, this method sentence", all cited).
#
# WHY THIS IS A FIXTURE, NOT REAL STARRYDATA ROWS: real Starrydata curve/sample
# rows are derived from a licensed source and are NOT committed to this public
# repo (the starrydata demo seed is gitignored). So the curve/sample below are a
# small, faithful, clearly-namespaced DEMO ABox (sd:-shaped, but living under the
# papers dataset's …/resource/demo/ space so nobody mistakes them for real rows).
# Their composition matches the seed paper (an n-type half-Heusler TiZrHf-NiSn);
# the figure and the condition sentence they point at ARE real nodes in the
# committed paper graph (seed/paper.ttl, from the CC-BY JATS of PMC5951533).
#
# Governance (§A.7-4): crosswalk is for entities and explicit normalized values;
# prose-location is the document layer's job. So the prose link
# (lit:conditionStatedIn) hangs off the SAMPLE (an entity), pointing INTO the
# document — it does NOT put a composition on a sentence, and it does NOT touch
# the crosswalk hub. Promoting this overlay leaves the hub's shared compositions
# and tools unchanged (MVP crosswalk-regression gate).

@prefix sd:   <https://kumagallium.github.io/asterism/starrydata/ontology#> .
@prefix prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix cito: <http://purl.org/spar/cito/> .
@prefix lit:  <https://kumagallium.github.io/asterism/papers/ontology#> .
@prefix xsd:  <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

# --- demo sample (sd:-shaped; faithful composition from the seed paper) ----------
<https://kumagallium.github.io/asterism/papers/resource/demo/sample/hh1>
  a sd:Sample ;
  sd:compositionString "Ti0.5Zr0.25Hf0.25NiSn" ;
  # prose-location: the measurement condition for this sample is stated in §4,
  # Materials and Methods, paragraph 2, sentence 1 (the PPMS / TTO sentence).
  lit:conditionStatedIn
    <https://kumagallium.github.io/asterism/papers/resource/paper/PMC5951533/sec/sec4-materials-11-00649/para/1/sent/0> .

# --- demo ZT curve, digitized from Figure 3 (the transport-properties figure) ----
<https://kumagallium.github.io/asterism/papers/resource/demo/curve/hh1>
  a sd:Curve ;
  sd:ofSample <https://kumagallium.github.io/asterism/papers/resource/demo/sample/hh1> ;
  sd:propertyY "ZT" ;
  sd:yMax "1.0"^^xsd:double ;
  # the curve was derived from a specific FIGURE node, not just "the paper" — the
  # §A.6 precision: prov:wasDerivedFrom + cito:usesDataFrom point at the figure.
  prov:wasDerivedFrom
    <https://kumagallium.github.io/asterism/papers/resource/paper/PMC5951533/fig/materials-11-00649-f003> ;
  cito:usesDataFrom
    <https://kumagallium.github.io/asterism/papers/resource/paper/PMC5951533/fig/materials-11-00649-f003> .
